  "sentences": [
    {
      "en": "Someone had once left a small gift inside the locker: a folded paper crane and a piece of chocolate.",
      "zh": "曾經有人在置物櫃裡留下一份小禮物：一隻摺紙鶴，還有一小塊巧克力。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Nobody signed their name, but the handwriting always looked honest and careful.",
      "zh": "沒有人簽名，但字跡看起來總是誠懇又用心。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Locker 113 was old, near the end of the hallway, with a mark on the door and a lock that never quite closed all the way.",
      "zh": "113號置物櫃很舊，在走廊盡頭附近，門上有個痕跡，鎖也從來沒辦法完全關緊。"
    },
    {
      "en": "According to the school list, it belonged to nobody. No name, no class, just an empty line.",
      "zh": "根據學校的名單，它不屬於任何人，沒有名字，沒有班級，只有一行空白。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"An empty locker with a broken lock,\" Bernice said. \"That's an easy case.\"",
      "zh": "Bernice 說：「一個沒人用又鎖不緊的置物櫃，這案子很簡單。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Coco opened it carefully. Inside was a single folded piece of paper and a small piece of chocolate.",
      "zh": "Coco 小心地打開它，裡面有一張折起來的紙，還有一小片巧克力。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The paper said: \"You're doing better than you think.\"",
      "zh": "紙上寫著：「你比自己想的做得更好。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"That's for whoever opens it next,\" Coco said quietly.",
      "zh": "Coco 小聲說：「這是留給下一個打開它的人的。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "They asked a few students walking by if they knew about the locker.",
      "zh": "他們問了幾個經過的學生知不知道這個置物櫃的事。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Everyone knows about 113,\" one student said. \"You open it on a hard day. There's always something inside.\"",
      "zh": "一個學生說：「大家都知道113號，你在難過的日子打開它，裡面總是有東西。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Who puts the things inside?\" Bernice asked.",
      "zh": "Bernice 問：「是誰把東西放進去的？」"
    },
    {
      "en": "The student didn't seem to know either. \"I don't know,\" she said. \"I put something in myself, once.\"",
      "zh": "那個學生也不太清楚：「我不知道，」她說：「我自己也放過一次東西進去。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Coco and Bernice looked at each other. This was not like the other cases.",
      "zh": "Coco 和 Bernice 對看了一眼，這跟其他案子不一樣。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"In every case before this,\" Coco said, \"there was one person behind it. One reason, one answer.\"",
      "zh": "Coco 說：「在這之前的每個案子，背後都有一個人，一個原因，一個答案。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Maybe this time there isn't just one,\" Bernice said slowly.",
      "zh": "Bernice 慢慢地說：「也許這次不是只有一個人。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "They decided to watch the locker for a few days, the same way they had watched the clock, months ago.",
      "zh": "他們決定觀察這個置物櫃幾天，就像幾個月前觀察那個鐘一樣。"
    },
    {
      "en": "On the first day, a boy they didn't know walked past, opened it, read the note inside, and put in a small card before closing it again.",
      "zh": "第一天，一個他們不認識的男生走過去，打開櫃子，讀了裡面的紙條，放進一張小卡片，然後把櫃子關上。"
    },
    {
      "en": "On the second day, a girl added a pencil. On the third day, someone left a short poem.",
      "zh": "第二天，一個女生放進一支鉛筆，第三天，有人留了一首短詩。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Nobody who added something took anything out. Nobody who took something seemed to know who had left it.",
      "zh": "放東西進去的人都沒有拿走任何東西，拿走東西的人似乎也不知道是誰放的。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"It's not one person,\" Coco said finally. \"It's whoever needs it, and then whoever has something to give.\"",
      "zh": "Coco 最後說：「這不是一個人，是需要的人，然後是有東西可以給的人。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Bernice sat down slowly on the floor near the locker. \"How do you solve a case,\" she asked, \"that isn't really a secret at all?\"",
      "zh": "Bernice 慢慢地坐到置物櫃旁邊的地上：「一個根本不算秘密的案子，」她問：「要怎麼解開？」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Coco didn't have an answer yet, but for the first time, she wasn't sure they needed one.",
      "zh": "Coco 還沒有答案，但這是第一次，她不確定他們真的需要一個答案。"
    },
    {
      "en": "One rainy week, the locker held a small folded umbrella instead of a note.",
      "zh": "有一個下雨的星期，置物櫃裡放的不是紙條，而是一把折疊小雨傘。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Another time, it was a single orange, with a smiley face drawn on the peel.",
      "zh": "還有一次，裡面是一顆柳橙，皮上畫著一張笑臉。"
    },
    {
      "en": "That weekend, Coco's family made a shopping list: butter, salt, a new dictionary for her brother, and a belt for her father.",
      "zh": "那個週末，Coco 家寫了一張採買清單：奶油、鹽、給弟弟的一本新字典，還有給爸爸的一條皮帶。"
    },
    {
      "en": "At the store, her mother also picked up a fork set, a small towel, and a pair of jeans on sale.",
      "zh": "在店裡，媽媽還買了一組叉子、一條小毛巾，還有一件特價的牛仔褲。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Coco added a T-shirt, a tie for a school event, and a cheap plastic tool kit her brother had been asking for.",
      "zh": "Coco 加買了一件 T 恤、一條要用在學校活動的領帶，還有弟弟一直吵著要的便宜塑膠工具組。"
    }
  ],
